#: ../../doc/utility.rst:144
msgid "Atomic Reference Counting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/utility.rst:146
msgid ""
"``atomic_counter`` wraps AngelScript's ``asAtomicInc`` / ``asAtomicDec`` for "
"thread-safe reference counting. It is designed for implementing the "
"``addref`` / ``release`` / ``get_refcount`` behaviours of a garbage-"
"collected ``ref_class``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/utility.rst:150
msgid ""
"Constructing an ``atomic_counter`` initializes the counter to 1. Prefix ``+"
"+`` and ``--`` call ``asAtomicInc`` and ``asAtomicDec`` respectively, "
"returning the new value. The ``dec_and_try_destroy`` method decrements and, "
"if the counter reaches 0, invokes a destroyer callback — typically "
"``delete`` on the enclosing object."
msgstr ""

